        {
          "type": "theory",
          "data": {
            "title": "The Code: Sun vs Moon Series",
            "text": "Khmer reading is a code: the main consonant (the 'commander') determines how the vowel after it will sound. There are two phonetic systems (series): Sun Team (A-Series) and Moon Team (O-Series). Sun letters feel lighter and keep vowels clean (e.g., -ា becomes -aa). Moon letters are heavier and shift the vowel by adding an E- or O-color at the start (e.g., -ា becomes -ea; -ាំ becomes -oam). Use the 80% visual rule to start: smooth heads often indicate Sun; teeth/extra strokes/complex shapes often indicate Moon. Exceptions exist (e.g., ប and ស look Moon-like but are Sun), but do not chase exceptions in the first two weeks—master the 80% rule first.",
            "sublesson_title": "Theory"
          }
        },
