          "type": "theory",
          "data": {
            "title": "Right-side Vowels (Inventory)",
            "text": "Right-side vowels are written to the right of the consonant like a cane. In R1 you learn three: ា (Aa), ះ (Ah), and ាំ (Am). With Sun letters: ា→-aa, ះ→-ah, ាំ→-am. With Moon letters: ា→-ea, ះ→-eah, ាំ→-oam. Core rule: Sun + vowel = vowel sound stays clean; Moon + vowel = vowel shifts with E/O coloring at the start.",
            "sublesson_title": "Theory"
          }
        },
